## Docker Install (Recommended)

### Prerequisites

- GitHub account linked to the EpicGames org:
  https://www.unrealengine.com/en-US/ue-on-github
- GitHub Personal Access Token (classic) with `read:packages` scope
- An EC2 instance (m7i.xlarge recommended) running Ubuntu 22.04

### Steps

1. **Launch a build instance** — use `{{ .BaseImage }}` as the base AMI.

2. **Install Docker CE:**
   ```bash
   curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh
   systemctl enable docker
   ```

3. **Log in to GitHub Container Registry:**
   ```bash
   echo "<YOUR_GITHUB_PAT>" | docker login ghcr.io -u <YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME> --password-stdin
   ```

4. **Get the Docker Compose file** from your UE source checkout:
   ```
   Engine/Source/Programs/Horde/HordeServer/docker-compose.yml
   ```
   Copy it to the instance at `/opt/horde/docker-compose.yml`.

5. **Create the Horde systemd service** at `/etc/systemd/system/horde.service`:
   ```ini
   [Unit]
   Description=Horde Server
   After=network-online.target docker.service
   Requires=docker.service

   [Service]
   Type=oneshot
   RemainAfterExit=yes
   WorkingDirectory=/opt/horde
   ExecStart=/usr/bin/docker compose up -d
   ExecStop=/usr/bin/docker compose down
   ExecReload=/usr/bin/docker compose pull && /usr/bin/docker compose up -d

   [Install]
   WantedBy=multi-user.target
   ```

6. **Enable the service:**
   ```bash
   systemctl daemon-reload
   systemctl enable horde
   ```

7. **Create the config directory:**
   ```bash
   mkdir -p /etc/horde
   ```

8. **Stop all services** before creating the AMI:
   ```bash
   systemctl stop horde docker
   ```

9. **Create the AMI:**
   ```bash
   aws ec2 create-image \
     --instance-id <instance-id> \
     --name "{{ .Name }}-$(date +%Y%m%d)" \
     --no-reboot
   ```

10. **Update `fabrica.yaml`:**
    ```yaml
    horde:
      amiId: ami-<id from previous step>
    ```
